# To PRD Workflow

## When to Use

- The user wants to plan a new feature, capability, or significant change to MyOrganizer.
- The user asks to write a PRD, create a feature spec, or turn an idea into a structured plan.
- The user wants to prepare work for `yarn dispatch-agents`.

## Core Approach

Read and follow `.github/skills/to-prd/SKILL.md` exactly.

Key points:
- Read `config.md` and `CONTEXT.md` first.
- Delegate codebase exploration to `CodeExplorer` (`.github/agents/explore.agent.md`).
- Present test seams to the user for approval — this is the only interactive step.
- Publish the PRD Issue via `gh issue create` directly (not via IssueCreator).
- Run `yarn ai:create-labels` first if any required labels are missing.

## Next Step

After the PRD Issue is published, use the **to-issues** skill to break it into Slice Issues, then `yarn dispatch-agents --prd <issue-number>` to hand off to autonomous agents.

## Skill Files

- `.github/skills/to-prd/SKILL.md` — full skill definition
- `.github/skills/to-prd/config.md` — label vocabulary and issue formats
